{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"25446eb7-7be8-4ae7-8f66-9f1327bc1cbb","content":"\n\nHere's the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test \\\n  -- \\\n  --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage \\\n  --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump \\\n  --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Key mapping:**\n\n| VSTest flag | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|\n| `--filter` | `--filter` (after `--`) |\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `--hangdump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\nEverything after `--` is forwarded directly to the platform runner. You'll also need the corresponding NuGet packages in your test project:\n\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump`","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"86a62034-7987-4055-abf5-0eed45e47ec4","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating a `dotnet test` command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing infrastructure, not a codebase question. Let me answer directly.\n\nKey differences when moving to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n1. **Filter syntax**: `--filter` becomes `--filter` still works but the flag might be slightly different. Actually, in Microsoft.Testing.Platform, the filter flag is `--filter` as well, but the runner is invoked differently.\n\n2. **How it's invoked**: With Microsoft.Testing.Platform, the test project itself becomes an executable. You can still use `dotnet test` but the arguments pass through differently, or you can run the executable directly.\n\n\n3. **Logger**: `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx` for TRX output.\n\n4. **Code coverage**: `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` becomes `--coverage` with `--coverage-output-format cobertura` to specify the format.\n\n5. **Blame**: The crash and hang blame flags get remapped to different options in the new platform.\n\nNow I'm working through the exact flag mappings when using `dotnet test` with Microsoft.Testing.Platform, particularly how filter syntax translates through the new runner.\n\nWhen running via `dotnet test`, arguments after `--` get passed directly to the test platform, so the modern approach would be to use `dotnet test` with the new flags like `--filter`, `--report-trx`, `--coverage`, and dump options all passed through the separator. Alternatively, I could run the test executable directly without going through `dotnet test`. So with newer .NET versions, `dotnet test` can work directly with Microsoft.Testing.Platform and understands flags like `--filter` natively, forwarding them appropriately, while platform-specific options still go after the `--` separator.","outputTokens":1273},"id":"5ab76bf3-80a3-497a-84f4-ea464d2c3812","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:49:25.151Z","parentId":"580e6e3f-9ada-418a-a00f-de96dc855c3f"}
